snippet: After French troops helped drive militants from cities in northern Mali, thousands gathered to greet François Hollande, but little was known of the fighters’ fate.
abstract: French Pres Francois Hollande pays triumphant visit to Timbuktu, Mali, and receives rapturous welcome from thousands of people; questions remain about what France has accomplished aside from chasing Islamic extremists from cities and into their desert and mountain redoubts.

byline.contributor: Steven Erlanger contributed reporting from Munich, Eric Schmitt from Washington, and Scott Sayare from Paris.

lead_paragraph: After French troops helped drive militants from cities in northern Mali, thousands gathered to greet François Hollande, but little was known of the fighters’ fate.

headline.seo: Hollande Hailed in Mali, but Doubts Are Raised on Victory
headline.main: Timbuktu Gives France’s President an Ecstatic Welcome
headline.print_headline: Hollande Is Hailed in Mali, but Doubts Persist on How Long Peace Will Last
